Treasury Secretary James Baker saidbanks must do more lending to developing countries.    Baker, in an interview on Cable News Network, was askedabout such loans after Standard and Poor's Corp todaydowngraded the debt of six major money centre bank holdingcompanies, largely because of their heavy loan exposure todeveloping nations.    Baker said developing countries must adopt free marketeconomic policies such as that of the United States. He saidcapital flows will be required to support the needed reforms inthose countries' economic systems.    The money must come either through equity or debt and Bakersaid developing nations' "investment regimes do not supportenough equity investment, so you've got to have some debtthere." REUTER&#3;